IMPRESSION/REPORT/PLAN
#1 Distal rectal cancer, young-onset
Mr. Stankiewicz presents for evaluation and treatment of rectal cancer.  I discussed the development of cancer with the patient and his wife, including the need for endoscopic ultrasound to stage the tumor.  Would request tattooing of the distal margin and description in relation to the seminal vesicles to assist surgical planning.  After review with Dr. Sanchez, we will also repeat the colonoscopy with NBI imaging to evaluate for subtle neoplasia given his young-onset.  Also discussed Lynch syndrome, and patient is agreeable to immunohistochemistry staining to rule this out.  Therefore, I would request biopsies at the time of his colonoscopy to be obtained for this.  He had trouble with sedation during his first examination and therefore Anesthesia assistance will be requested.  Stoma nurse will be requested for education regarding colostomy versus temporary ileostomy, and patient will meet with Colon and Rectal Surgery.
#2 Elevated blood pressure
Blood pressure was 151/100, and therefore we will check a six-hour ambulatory.  Hypertension Clinic consultation is requested if persistent elevation is noted.
Discussed with Dr. Sanchez, note to follow.
